10/10/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The Belgrade regional court convicted eight men Monday (October 9th) of the January 2000 murder of Serbian paramilitary leader and underground boss Zeljko "Arkan" Raznatovic and his two bodyguards.
Three defendants were sentenced to 30 years in prison, while the other five received lighter sentences.
At the time of his murder, Raznatovic was facing charges by the UN tribunal for atrocities during the Bosnian conflict.
(Danas - 10/10/06;
Tanjug, B92, Reuters, BBC, UPI - 09/10/06)
